It could also belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-category as it proposes a non-negative matrix factorization model. The paper also involves analyzing user behavior, which could place it in the Social and Information Networks (cs.SI) sub-category. Additionally, the paper discusses the usability of the proposed framework, which could place it in the Human-Computer Interaction (cs.HC) sub-category. Finally, the paper involves natural language processing, which could place it in the Computation and Language (cs.CL) sub-category.
